The paper deals with the problem of online graph colouring, which is a topic in computer science related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of a buffer to delay the colouring of nodes suggests a possible connection to queueing theory and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The analysis of the number of colours used in different types of graphs involves graph theory (cs.GT). The proposed algorithm involves making probabilistic choices, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of probability suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT).
